    <h1>Paper Walls: The Architecture of Control</h1>
   
    <p>This is a literary memoir that examines how identity, belonging, and truth are shaped inside systems that prioritize narrative over lived experience.</p>
   
    <div class="quote">
        "This is not a story about what happened. It is a record of how reality is constructed—and what it takes to step outside of it."
    </div>

    <p>Alongside the memoir is the <strong>Paper Walls Record Archive</strong>—a parallel body of documentation drawn from court filings, public records, and historical fragments.</p>
